{"content":"<li class=\"n-box-item date-title\" data-end=\"1564372799\" data-start=\"1564286400\" data-txt=\"Monday, December 23, 2019\">Sunday, July 28, 2019</li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"3482566\" data-ts=\"1564364495\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/EXAS\" target=\"_blank\">EXAS</a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/3482566-exact-sciences-closing-in-on-genomic-health-for-2_8b-bloomberg\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">Exact Sciences closing in on Genomic Health for $2.8B - Bloomberg</a></h4><ul><li>Bloomberg <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-27/exact-sciences-is-said-to-be-in-talks-to-buy-genomic-health\" target=\"_blank\">reports </a>that Exact Sciences (NASDAQ:<a href='https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EXAS' title='Exact Sciences Corporation'>EXAS</a>) is in advanced talks to acquire Genomic Health (NASDAQ:<a href='https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GHDX' title='Genomic Health, Inc.'>GHDX</a>) for $2.8B. A deal could be announced as early as next week.</li><li>EXAS generates all of its revenue from its Cologuard molecular testing service for the early detection of colorectal cancer.</li><li>GHDX provides cancer-focused molecular testing services via its Oncotype DX test for breast cancer, ductal carcinoma in situ, colon cancer and prostate cancer. Almost 90% of its Q1 revenues were generated in breast cancer.</li></ul><div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"3482566\" data-linked=\"Exact Sciences closing in on Genomic Health for $2.8B - Bloomberg\" data-tweet=\"$EXAS $GHDX - Exact Sciences closing in on Genomic Health for $2.8B - Bloomberg https://seekingalpha.com/news/3482566-exact-sciences-closing-in-on-genomic-health-for-2_8b-bloomberg?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/3482566-exact-sciences-closing-in-on-genomic-health-for-2_8b-bloomberg\"><div class=\"ico